  "prompt": "What are the most important characteristics of organisms?",
  "response": "The most important characteristics of organisms include:\n\n1. Organization\n- Composed of one or more cells\n- Structured with specific levels of complexity\n\n2. Metabolism\n- Ability to process energy\n- Convert nutrients into usable forms\n- Perform chemical reactions to sustain life\n\n3. Homeostasis\n- Maintaining internal stability\n- Regulating internal conditions\n- Adapting to environmental changes\n\n4. Growth and Development\n- Increasing in size\n- Changing and differentiating over time\n- Developing specialized structures\n\n5. Reproduction\n- Ability to produce offspring\n- Passing genetic information to next generation\n- Ensuring species continuation\n\n6. Response to Stimuli\n- Detecting and reacting to environmental changes\n- Adapting to external conditions\n- Showing sensitivity\n\n7. Adaptation\n- Evolving to survive in specific environments\n- Developing traits that enhance survival\n- Responding to natural selection pressures\n\n8. Genetic Information\n- Carrying hereditary instructions\n- Having DNA/RNA\n- Transmitting characteristics to descendants\n\n9. Energy Processing\n- Obtaining and using energy\n- Converting chemical energy\n- Supporting life processes\n\n10. Cellular Structure\n- Composed of fundamental units (cells)\n- Having specific organizational mechanisms\n\nThese characteristics collectively define living organisms and distinguish them from non-living entities.",
